animal.description:
NAME: Holly
BREED: Border Collie
GENDER: Spayed Female
DOB: Oct. 14, 2015
WEIGHT:   47 lbs
COAT: Smooth
COLOR: Red Merle
ACTIVITY LEVEL: Active Companion
LOCATION: Chesterfield, VA

Meet Holly!

 Holly is a cute little 5-year-old, purebred, red merle, female BC (She kind of reminds me of a little fox). Before Holly came to BRBCR, she lived with her family and three other dogs. Holly was purchased from a breeder. Holly bonded with the people in her household, but unfortunately was aggressive to an older smaller female dog. Over the last two years, things became progressively worse between Holly and the other dog. The family had to keep all the dogs separated and rotate them, which became difficult over time, and the owner sought the assistance of a rescue to find a good home for Holly.

Holly is house trained and vocal when she needs to go out. She wants someone to walk with her into the yard which is good because she kind of likes to dig. She recalls very well, walks on a leash nicely, and knows basic commands (sit, down, stay, come, leave it, etc.).

If you are a proponent of crate training, you should know that Holly does not like being in crates, and whimpers when she is crated. However, she has needed to be crated because she cannot be left unsupervised with other dogs. Currently, there is usually someone at home all day, so we have not needed to utilize it too much. Other than aggression toward other dogs, we have not observed any serious problem or behaviors.

She is a particularly good alarm dog as she barks at anyone walking past our home, but easily quiets when you command her to stop. She loves to play and catch things, especially balls, and she is quite good at it. She spends most of her day curled up near me while I work, and she is pretty quiet and laid back.

Holly does not get along well with other dogs. She exhibits the same behaviors in her foster home that she had in her previous home. Therefore, Holly will only be adopted to a home where she is and will be the only dog. We have a cat and she seems ok with him. Although, I have not observed Holly around small children, she should not be adopted to a home with small children. We have a teenager and she would be fine in a home with older children. We have a fenced in yard, but she likes to dig and needs supervision.

If you are interested in adopting Holly, please fill out an application on our website (www.BRBCR.org) and then contact her foster parents, Princy Doss and Scott Fullen at dossfullen@outlook.com. All potential adopters are required to have a home visit prior to placement of one of our rescues. Holly's adoption fee is $300, and we offer a two-week trial period when you adopt one of our dogs.

Please note that we only use our website (www.BRBCR.org) and PetFinder to list our available dogs. Contact us through these two sites only. We are not associated with any other listing websites.

Thank you for considering a rescue!

We provide no guarantees regarding behavior, breed, or age of the dogs. Thank you for rescuing.Thank you for looking to Adopt a Labrador Retriever or other Mixed Breed Dog from California Labradors Retrievers and More Rescue. Please take a moment and go to www.labsandmore.org and click on Adopt to complete our online dog adoption application. If you have any questions email us at doginfo@labsandmore.org or call us at 858-273-5386. Thank you for looking to a rescue group to fulfill your dream of adding a new dog to your life! Dogs + Love = Family

animal.description:
Dot is an approximately 12 year old female Maltipoo. She is spayed, up to date on vaccines and microchipped. She weighs about 6 lbs. Dot was a stray rescued by Maltese Rescue California and is currently staying with her foster in Tucson, AZ. She would do best as an "only dog" because she gets jealous and will growl at other dogs if they are in her space.  She is a fear biter if picked up unexpectedly.  Her foster is working to stop this behavior.  We don’t know how she gets along with cats. She is housetrained and walks well on a leash. She knows basic commands and learns very quickly. An ideal situation for Dot would be a small child free, quiet home. She needs someone with the time and patience to make her feel safe and secure. It takes her a little while to relax and feel comfortable in her surroundings. Once she feels safe, she is a great snuggler and loves to sit on your lap and give kisses.

If you would like to meet and adopt Dot, please go to our website and submit our adoption application www.malteserescuecalifornia.org. Remember, it’s all about second chances.

To arrange a meet and greet with a dog, you MUST fill out the adoption application so that it can be sent to the foster parent for review to determine if your home is a match for the dog. If a dog receives multiple applications, we operate on a best-fit basis, not first come first served.***

**Gomie is initially fearful of new people, so a confident leader is a must. He will sometimes bark, which can make people nervous. He is good with dogs, but needs slow introductions.**

Hi I'm Gomie. I am a sweet boy with a heart of gold, but I am lacking in confidence. I need an experienced owner that will take the lead, so I don't think I have to. Please read the rest of my bio to understand more about me!

I was found in a wooded ditch and I was in bad shape. I heard a nice lady talking to her other doggy. She sounded nice so I stuck my little nose out from under the bushes I was hiding under and scared her half to death! After lots of coaxing with treats, I let her and her husband scoop me up and take me home.

Now I am safe with rescue and I'm looking for my forever home, could it be you? I'm just looking for someone to let me jump on the sofa and get lots of snuggles. I especially love to snuggle at night when it gets chilly. I am a shadow dog and I love to follow my foster mom as much as possible. If she's working at her desk I like to sit by her feet. 

I love going on walks. I get to meet so many dogs and people. I will accept pets from anyone that wants to give them to me. I love to chase dogs around the park. I haven't been able to do that lately since I had my FHO surgery (to fix my dislocated hip). I'm slowly getting used to using my leg again, but my adoptive family will need to continue to do my stretches with me. Right now I have a foster brother and I would love a home with another dog. I do okay amusing myself when needed as long as I have lots of toys to play with.

I love to chew on anything I can find. I especially love to pull out tissues I find on the ground and shred them, so foster mom hides all the trash cans.

I'm mostly potty trained. I've got a time limit. When that time limit expires I go, whether I'm inside or outside. So best to walk me every 8 hours or less.

I would love a home where I don't have to be crated all the time. I love being free. But if I have to go in there I guess I can, but I will give you puppy dog eyes to try to persuade you otherwise. You've been warned.

I'm good on walks, though I do pull sometimes when I'm excited. What do you expect? I'm new to the world and I just want to see, smell and explore it all. I would love an active person that likes to take me on walks since I love to be outside. Anytime I see another dog outside I wish I could go meet them and play. 

I am neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations, microchipped, and current on my monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. My adoption fee is $300. If you think I could be the one for you, please fill out an app on our website: www.secondchancenc.org.

Meet baby Jubilee. She's only about eight weeks old and cute as a button! She may be a mix between border collie and pit bull, but no one knows for sure. She already knows how to use the doggie door and is learning to go outside to potty!

Jubilee loves playing with kids, toys, other dogs and even cats! Her favorite thing to do, however, is snuggle with her foster family. She's smart and lovable and will soon be able to learn lots of tricks and how to walk on a leash. 

Jubilee will be available LOCALLY ONLY as foster to adopt February 10th. Later, when she has been spayed, the adoption can be finalized and she will be yours forever and ever!

However, we're already accepting applications. If you are interested in checking out this adorable little girl to see if she could be your new best friend, call or text Julie at 435-773-5209 Tuesday through Saturday between 9:00 and 5:00 to arrange a meeting.

MEET FLEMMING:

Flemming is a small Terrier mix puppy that was born on 11/17/2020. Him and his sister entered into a high-intake shelter at a young age. Puppies have weak immune systems are easily compromised in a shelter environment and they needed to get out! These sweet babies are little bundles of energy with big personalities! Puppies need homes where someone is home more often than not for proper house training and socialization. They are not leash trained, crate trained or house trained. They are typical puppies that are prone to chew things they shouldn't and exhibit typical puppy behavior. They will need training and consistency in order to make well rounded family pets that will provide years of love and happiness! 

Flemming is:
Current Distemper
Dewormed
Receiving Heartworm and Flea Prevention
Microchipped
Neutered

ADOPTION FEE: $375

FUREVER TAILS IS A NON-PROFIT, NO-KILL, FOSTER HOME BASED ANIMAL RESCUE BASED OUT OF OAKLAND TOWNSHIP, MI. OUR FOSTER ANIMALS ARE LIVING IN FOSTER HOMES AND TREATED LIKE FAMILY UNTIL THEY FIND THEIR OWN FUREVER FAMILIES. ADOPTION FEES ARE NECESSARY TO HELP US COVER VETTING COSTS FOR OUR RESCUED ANIMALS. UNFORTUNATELY AT THIS TIME WE ARE NOT CURRENTLY ADOPTING OUT OF THE STATE OF MI.

animal.description:
Ollie is a 2 year old, sweet, ADORABLE Basset Hound. 

Ollie was surrendered to the shelter when he was a young pup because he jumped out the car window and broke his back leg, his family didn't want to pay for it or take care of it, so instead they dumped him at the shelter. The shelter did fix his leg and got him completely vetted. He was so lucky the shelter has those resources becuase most overcrowded shelters don't. He was then adopted to what he thought was his forever family. Due to no fault of his own he was recently dumped back at the shelter. The shelter knew he would be able to find a better home here in CO so they asked us to take him. 

Ollie has been in Colorado for a little while now and is ready to find his forever home. His foster said he is a happy, super playful, energetic pup. They have a small senior little dog, and they say he cannot figure out why she won't play with him. His foster said he also loves to spoon and snuggle lol. He does great with her grandkids and is honestly just an awesome, loving, goofy dog who deserves the best home possible. He would love a home with another dog to play with but it's not mandatory as he is pretty happy no matter what.

If you are interested in adopting Ollie, please fill out our adoption application at brighterdaysdogrescue.com

Ollie's adoption fee is $495.00

animal.description: This mush is Wally. He is about 3 years old and weighs 47 pounds. He has the most adorable bulldog face and pittie head, but of course he is a mix. Hes from a really rural area where unfortunately a lot of dogs dont make it out of the shelter. He is a lucky boy that we saved him though and we are so glad we did. He is a total goofy, sweetheart. He wants nothing more than to get love and attention and give it right back to his humans. He is wonderful with other dogs too - he LOVES to play. He does not bother cats. He isn't overly hyper or lazy. He's a great mix of playful and "lets nap on the couch." He loves to play with toys and run around the yard. We think a home with a yard would be great for him. He is doing great in foster care with his house training. He has been through a lot the last few weeks and needs a place to just relax. He does play rough. No one ever taught him to stop puppy biting and now he is a big dog. He needs someone who will make sure he gets out of this habit. His foster is working with him and he is learning, but he will need someone who can tell him "no". Due to this, we want him to go to a home with kids over 12. He would never purposely hurt anyone, but he needs time to grow out of the habit. If you would like to meet him, fill out an application at bcaaofnj.org

*Due to state laws regarding out of state adoptions, we cannot adopt to families in Massachusetts or Rhode Island.*

Carla is a mixed breed pup ready for her forever home. She is approximately 2 years old. She is a playful, happy girl who would bring joy to your life. 

Listed breed is an educated guess made by our veterinarian and is NOT a guarantee - this also means we have no way of knowing what a puppy's adult size will be.

This dog is currently being fostered in Mississippi and will be transported via Barton's Barkers transport services upon adoption. Their adoption fee is $450 and includes spay/neuter, age appropriate vaccinations, a nose to tail vet check, microchip and transport costs. Second Chances lists dogs as being available in White River Junction, VT because we transport our dogs to the area every 3rd week after they have been adopted. All of our local shelters have a high euthanasia rate due to overpopulation so we created our rescue group to primarily adopt to the northern states to help keep as many dogs as we can from entering our kill shelters.

animal.description: This sweet, little dotted girl is looking for her forever home. Dottie has tons of puppy energy, but loves to snuggle up in your lap. Some of her favorite things include making 2 year olds squeal and giggle with her kisses, running after a toy, and being your work-from-home coworker/lap warmer. So far, Dottie's only dislike is the cold weather. She hustles back inside as quick as she can after a potty break. Her leash skills are outstanding for her age (though it sometimes takes a few steps to convince her the cold air is worth it!) Dottie is still very much a puppy, but she has made great progress with her potty training. She has very few accidents when she is taken out consistently and often. She hasn't fallen in love with the crate yet, but her foster family continues to work on it. She enjoys the company of her foster siblings, both furry and human. She is respectful of senior dogs and their space, but would definitely enjoy a companion to play with. She has shown some interest in the cats in her foster home, but no aggression. If you are interested in this animal please start by filling out an adoption application at CFP-NC.org/adopt and we will get in touch with you.

animal.description: Josie is all puppy! She spends a good portion of her time sleeping (she loves to cuddle), but when she is awake she is full of energy and very playful! She loves to chew on toys (she is definitely teething hard!) and run around the house exploring. She is spunky and hilarious. She hates the cold weather and will sit right by your feet and wait patiently for you to bring her back inside. She has been friendly but submissive/a little nervous when meeting new dogs. She warms up quickly though. Just teething like crazy (biting nonstop) so no small kids If you are interested in this animal please start by filling out an adoption application at CFP-NC.org/adopt and we will get in touch with you.
